{
  "text": "Much of this work is in its infancy; transcriptomic investigation of biomarkers of liver allograft tolerance began less than a decade ago [CITATION_1] . Already though, biomarker-based diagnostic tests have gained regulatory approval and have reached the market [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . A diagnostic kit based on an 11-transcript set identified with microarray technology is used to non-invasively identify rejection in heart transplant recipients [CITATION_5] . As we will see, biomarkers of liver transplant tolerance have also yielded extremely promising results showing good potential for clinical translation in the near future. Liver transplant tolerance transcriptomic biomarkers Frontiers in Immunology | www.frontiersin.org",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8324429",
